			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Sybil Smith</strong></span> lives in Vermont and works as a nurse in a jail, which she says is not as scary as it may sound: &ldquo;Pathos abounds and stories leap out at me from behind the bars.&rdquo; She&rsquo;s currently in search of a publisher for her novel <em>My Mother&rsquo;s Early Lovers</em>, which was made into a movie that won first prize at the Film Fest New Haven and acclaim at the Maine International Film Festival.</p><a href="/contributors/sybil-smith" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
